    <item>
      <title>Docs: 用现有模型进行推理</title>
      <link>https://Joevaen.github.io/docs/quickstart/infer/existing_infer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://Joevaen.github.io/docs/quickstart/infer/existing_infer/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;所谓推理，指的是用训练好的模型在图像中进行目标检测，模型通过配置文件来定义，模型参数被保存在一个checkpoint文件中。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;吐过你想快速进行使用，我们建议使用&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/open-mmlab/mmdetection/tree/master/configs/faster_rcnn&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Faster RCNN&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;，同时使用这个&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/open-mmlab/mmdetection/blob/master/configs/faster_rcnn/faster_rcnn_r50_fpn_1x_coco.py&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;配置文件&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 和&lt;a href=&#34;http://download.openmmlab.com/mmdetection/v2.0/faster_rcnn/faster_rcnn_r50_fpn_1x_coco/faster_rcnn_r50_fpn_1x_coco_20200130-047c8118.pth&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;权重文件&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;。建议把权重文件下载到 &lt;code&gt;checkpoints&lt;/code&gt; 路径。&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Docs: 在标准数据集上进行现有模型的测试</title>
      <link>https://Joevaen.github.io/docs/quickstart/infer/test_on_standard/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://Joevaen.github.io/docs/quickstart/infer/test_on_standard/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;To evaluate a model&amp;rsquo;s accuracy, one usually tests the model on some standard datasets.
MMDetection supports multiple public datasets including COCO, Pascal VOC, CityScapes, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/open-mmlab/mmdetection/tree/master/configs/_base_/datasets&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;more&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.
This section will show how to test existing models on supported datasets.&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Docs: 在标准数据集上训练预定义模型</title>
      <link>https://Joevaen.github.io/docs/quickstart/infer/predefined/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://Joevaen.github.io/docs/quickstart/infer/predefined/</guid>
      <description>
        
        
        &lt;p&gt;MMDetection also provides out-of-the-box tools for training detection models.
This section will show how to train &lt;em&gt;predefined&lt;/em&gt; models (under &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/open-mmlab/mmdetection/tree/master/configs&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;configs&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) on standard datasets i.e. COCO.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Important&lt;/strong&gt;: The default learning rate in config files is for 8 GPUs and 2 img/gpu (batch size = 8*2 = 16).
According to the &lt;a href=&#34;https://arxiv.org/abs/1706.02677&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;linear scaling rule&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-external-link-alt&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, you need to set the learning rate proportional to the batch size if you use different GPUs or images per GPU, e.g., &lt;code&gt;lr=0.01&lt;/code&gt; for 4 GPUs * 2 imgs/gpu and &lt;code&gt;lr=0.08&lt;/code&gt; for 16 GPUs * 4 imgs/gpu.&lt;/p&gt;

      </description>
    </item>
    
